<h5 class="pt-3">About this research.</h5>

<p>The Forgetting Project is a research program investigating human memory and forgetting, conducted by PhD students and staff at Goldsmiths, Univeristy of London.</p>

<p>The lead researcher is currently PhD student Terry McGibbon (email: tmcgi001@gold.ac.uk), under the supervision of neuropsychologist Dr Ashok Jansari (a.jansari@gold.ac.uk).</p>

<p>The current study measures participants memory for pairs of words, tested at various delays.</p>

